div.p:
His health had at one period suffered much, as he says,
Commer. Phil. ep. 14. from those midnight hours of mental labour stolen from sleep; yet such was the vigour of his constitution, that he continued to pursue his usual mathematical studies till the 3 ge of eighty. He was then attacked by a complaint at first apparently trifling; but his strength daily and rapidly declined till the 1st of January 1748, when he fell asleep,: and thus expired without agony, or even a discomposing pang;
Hist. de l’Acad. 1748. a death not unlike that of the illustrious chemist Black, who died with his usual meal of milk balanced in his hand, as if to show by an experiment how easy his exit from life had been.
